022package com.restfb;
023
024import java.util.stream.Stream;
025
026public enum Version {
027
028  /**
029   * unversiond api
030   */
031  UNVERSIONED(null),
032
033  /**
034   * <tt>Graph API 3.1</tt>, available until October 23, 2020
035   *
036   * @since July 26, 2018
037   */
038  VERSION_3_1("v3.1"),
039
040  /**
041   * <tt>Graph API 3.2</tt>, available until April 30, 2021
042   *
043   * @since October 23, 2018
044   */
045  VERSION_3_2("v3.2"),
046
047  /**
048   * <tt>Graph API 3.3</tt>, available until July 29, 2021
049   *
050   * @since April 30, 2019
051   */
052  VERSION_3_3("v3.3"),
053
054  /**
055   * <tt>Graph API 4.0</tt>, available until October 29, 2021
056   *
057   * @since July 29, 2019
058   */
059  VERSION_4_0("v4.0"),
060
061  /**
062   * <tt>Graph API 5.0</tt>, available until February 3rd, 2022
063   *
064   * @since October 29, 2019
065   */
066  VERSION_5_0("v5.0"),
067
068  /**
069   * <tt>Graph API 6.0</tt>, available until May 5th, 2022
070   *
071   * @since February 3rd, 2020
072   */
073  VERSION_6_0("v6.0"),
074
075  /**
076   * <tt>Graph API 7.0</tt>, available until August 4th, 2022
077   *
078   * @since May 5th, 2020
079   */
080  VERSION_7_0("v7.0"),
081
082  /**
083   * <tt>Graph API 8.0</tt>, available until November 10th, 2022
084   *
085   * @since August 4th, 2020
086   */
087  VERSION_8_0("v8.0"),
088
089  /**
090   * <tt>Graph API 9.0</tt>, available until February 23, 2023
091   *
092   * @since November 10th, 2020
093   */
094  VERSION_9_0("v9.0"),
095
096  /**
097   * <tt>Graph API 10.0</tt>, available at least until February 2023
098   *
099   * @since February 23th, 2021
100   */
101  VERSION_10_0("v10.0"),
102
103  /**
104   * convenience enum to provide simple access to the latest supported Graph API Version.
105   * <p>
106   * the current version is <tt>Graph API 10.0</tt>
107   * </p>
108   */
109  LATEST("v10.0");
110
111  private final String urlElement;
112
113  Version(String urlElement) {
114    this.urlElement = urlElement;
115  }
116
117  public String getUrlElement() {
118    return this.urlElement;
119  }
120
121  public boolean isUrlElementRequired() {
122    return null != this.urlElement;
123  }
124
125  /**
126   * converts a String (for example the url parameter) into a Version object
127   * 
128   * @param urlElementStr
129   *          String that should
130   * @return the generated version
131   */
132  public static Version getVersionFromString(String urlElementStr) {
133    if (urlElementStr != null) {
134      return Stream.of(Version.values()).filter(v -> urlElementStr.equals(v.getUrlElement())).findFirst()
135              .orElse(UNVERSIONED);
136    }
137
138    return UNVERSIONED;
139  }
140}
